  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TEACH (Technical Assistance for European Caritas Organisations)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EUAV TEACH - Technical Assistance for European Caritas Organisations in Humanitarian Aid has the overall objective to strengthen the technical capacities in the areas of humanitarian learning and volunteer management. Three specific
objectives have been defined:
1. To build strong volunteer management systems among European Caritas organisations to improve volunteer identification, selection, training, placement and post-deployment
2. To enable European Caritas organisations to participate in the EUAV programme by strengthening their knowledge and capacity in relevant technical and quality standards 
3. To strengthen the capacities in raising awareness and communication on EUAV and Humanitarian Aid

CAFOD is primarily participating in activities relating to objective 2. 

The impact foreseen is to enable partners to become certified sending organisations in the EUAV programme and to improve the implementation of humanitarian aid in following the Core Humanitarian Standards. Activities include workshops on volunteer management and campaigning, development/adaptation of policies regarding volunteers, improving HR processes for volunteers and develop post-deployment strategies, self assessments and improvement of standards for CHS and EUAV.

The TEACH project involves 6 European Caritas organisations in Austria, Czech Republic, Ireland, the UK and Romania as well as Caritas Europa to ensure wider dissemination and learning among the 49 European member organisations.</narrative>
  </description>
